# Rulebook

Rules = `.mdc` in `.cursor/rules/`. Frontmatter: `description`, `globs` (or `alwaysApply: true`).

**Test:** Would the AI get this wrong without it? No → skip. Yes → add only the non-obvious part.

**Document:** Naming, order of ops, constraints, workflows ("When X: do A"). Not: syntax, tutorials, reference.

**Format:** 5–10 bullets max. Point to code, don't paste. No spoonfeeding.

**Add when:** Same mistake twice, or convention invisible in code. Not for one-off patterns.

**Avoid:** Long examples, repeating code, rules per domain, >15 lines.

**Names:** `preamble.mdc` (always), `use-X.mdc` (tools), `{domain}.mdc` (domain).

**Cursor best practices:** Under 500 lines. Reference files with @filename. No style guides (use linter), no common-command docs, no edge-case instructions. Add rules only after repeated mistakes.
